JOHANNESBURG – A video posted by twitter user No Chill in Mzansi has become popular because a non-Venda young man speaks fluent TshiVenda. While it is not surprising that a white person can speak a vernac language, it is the style in which he told the story that gathered interest. In his story he describes how he was hanging out with his friends enjoying pap, morogo and chakalaka. Can’t -------- pic.twitter.com/YGtMWLHEK1 He says while they were sitting a group of men driving flashy rides showed-off and spited them. The people listening to him tell his story were highly entertained by the fact that he speaks Venda better than most non-Venda South Africans. eNCA